The following assumptions were made regarding the financial plan:
&nbsp;
* Predicted sales growth of 20\%
&nbsp;
* Constant dividend payout ratio and interest expense 
&nbsp;
* Predicted increase in the cost, assets, and accounts payables proportional to sales
&nbsp;
*No new external debt or equity financing

Now, let us compute the increase in the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Increase in Sales}&=\text{Sales}\times\text{Rate of Increase}\\[12pt]
&={\$980,760}\times{20\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$196,152}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The increase in the sales amounts to \$196,152.**

Now, let us compute the projected sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Sales}&=\text{Sales}+\text{Increase in Sales}\\[12pt]
&={\$980,760}+{\$196,152}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$1,176,912}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected sales is \$1,176,912.**

Now, let us compute the percentage of cost in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Cost}&=\frac{\text{Cost}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$792,960}{\$980,760}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.81}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{81\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of cost in proportion to the sales is 81\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected cost:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Cost}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$1,176,912}\times{81\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$953,298.72}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected cost is \$953,298.72.**

Now, let us compute the percentage of Other Expenses in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Other Expenses}&=\frac{\text{Other Expenses}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$20,060}{\$980,760}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.02}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{2\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of Other Expenses in proportion to the sales is 2\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected Other Expenses:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Other Expenses}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$1,176,912}\times{2\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$23,538.24}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Other Expenses is \$23,538.24.**

Now, let us compute the projected taxable income:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Taxable Income}&=\text{Earnings before Interest and Taxes}\\[5pt]
&-\text{Interest Paid}\\[12pt]
&={\$200,075.04}-{\$14,740}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$189,932.04}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Taxable income is \$189,932.04.**

Now, let us compute the taxes:
